response: "{ \"title\": \"Fibonacci Generator (Medium)\", \"description\": \"The Fibonacci sequence is a series of numbers where the next number is the sum of the previous two. Write a function `fibonacci` that takes an integer `n` as input and generates the first `n` Fibonacci numbers.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```\\ndef fibonacci(n: int) -> list[int]:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): The number of Fibonacci numbers to generate.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- A list of integers representing the first `n` Fibonacci numbers.\\n\", \"code\": \"def fibonacci(n: int) -> list[int]:\\n    if n <= 0:\\n        return []\\n    elif n == 1:\\n        return [0]\\n    elif n == 2:\\n        return [0, 1]\\n\\n    fib_sequence = [0, 1]\\n    while len(fib_sequence) < n:\\n        fib_sequence.append(fib_sequence[-1] + fib_sequence[-2])\\n\\n    return fib_sequence[:n]\", \"tests\": [\"assert len(fibonacci(10)) == 10\", \"assert fibonacci(5) == [0, 1, 1, 2, 3]\", \"assert fibonacci(-1) == []\", \"assert fibonacci(0) == []\"] }"
